    "title": "Senior Plant Manager at Nestle India",
    "description": "Nestle India has an exciting opening for a Plant Manager at our Vijayawada office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Nestle India:\nNestle India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in 5S\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Learning & development budget\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Nestle India!",
